The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques for generating fill-in-the-blank quizzes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and ML for natural language understanding and generation. The paper also proposes concrete deep learning models, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of AI techniques for generating quizzes, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of data obtained from a language learning platform, which suggests that cs.ED (Education) could be another relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques for obtaining data, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
